meanings.definition: The action of subscribing in excess of the available supply or capacity.
meanings.sent1: The oversubscription of tickets led to many disappointed fans.
meanings.sent2: The oversubscription of the event caused chaos at the entrance.
meanings.sent3: The oversubscription of the school bus made for a comical scene with students sitting on each other's laps.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm for the club was an oversubscription that overflowed with joy.
meanings.sent5: The oversubscription of the buffet left no food for latecomers.

meanings.definition: The condition of being subscribed to in excess of the available supply or capacity.
meanings.sent1: The oversubscription of the magazine resulted in delayed deliveries.
meanings.sent2: The oversubscription of the parking lot led to cars being turned away.
meanings.sent3: The oversubscription of the elevator made for a humorous situation with people squeezed in like sardines.
meanings.sent4: His popularity was an oversubscription that filled every room with laughter.
meanings.sent5: The oversubscription of the library books meant some students had to wait weeks for their turn.
